get bookmark field "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
==================================================================

NAME
----

get bookmark field - Retrieve single bookmark data item or field.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Retrieve single bookmark data item or field.

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_bookmark_field( $field, $bookmark, $context ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$field` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The name of the data field to return
    Default: *None*

 `$bookmark` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The bookmark ID to get field
    Default: *None*

 `$context` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. The context of how the field will be used.
    Default: display

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.3](/Version_2.3 "Version 2.3")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_bookmark_field()` is located in `wp-includes/bookmark.php`

